<!-- FAQ Section -->
<section class="property-section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header">
            <h2 class="section-title fade-in">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        </div>
        
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
                <div class="accordion fade-in" id="propertyFAQ">
                    <div class="accordion-item border-0 mb-3 shadow-sm rounded">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                            <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne">
                                What documents do I need to buy a property?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" aria-labelledby="headingOne" data-bs-parent="#propertyFAQ">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                To purchase a property, you typically need identification documents, proof of income, bank statements, tax returns, and, if applicable, proof of down payment. Additional documents may be required depending on the specific circumstances of the transaction.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item border-0 mb-3 shadow-sm rounded">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo">
                                How long does the buying process take?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingTwo" data-bs-parent="#propertyFAQ">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                The property buying process typically takes between 30 to 90 days from offer acceptance to closing. Factors that can affect this timeline include financing approval, property inspections, appraisal, and title search. Cash transactions may close faster than those requiring mortgage financing.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item border-0 mb-3 shadow-sm rounded">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree">
                                Can I rent a property before buying it?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingThree" data-bs-parent="#propertyFAQ">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Yes, some properties offer rent-to-own options, allowing you to rent with the option to purchase later. These arrangements typically include a portion of your rent going toward a future down payment. While not all properties offer this option, it can be a good way to build equity while deciding if the property is right for you.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="accordion-item border-0 mb-3 shadow-sm rounded">
                        <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFour">
                            <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour">
                                What additional costs should I expect when buying a property?
                            </button>
                        </h2>
                        <div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="headingFour" data-bs-parent="#propertyFAQ">
                            <div class="accordion-body">
                                Beyond the property price, expect additional costs including closing fees, lawyer fees, property transfer tax, mortgage insurance, home inspection fees, appraisal fees, and potentially homeowner association fees. It's advisable to budget an extra 2-5% of the property price for these closing costs.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

@section Scripts {
    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function() {
            // Add 'show' class to all fade-in elements with a staggered delay
            const fadeElements = document.querySelectorAll('.fade-in');
            fadeElements.forEach((el, index) => {
                setTimeout(() => {
                    el.style.opacity = '1';
                }, 100 + (index * 100));
            });
        });
    </script>
} 